Cell["\<\
The syntax above defines the z-axis to be parallel to the {1,1,1} vector and \
the x-axis to be in the plane of the Y-axis {0,1,0} and the {1,1,1} vector. \
The y-axis is perpendicular to the other two, defining a right-handed axis \
system. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6414609137674093`*^9, 3.641460983749724*^9}, 
   3.641461069671649*^9},
 Background->RGBColor[
  1, 0.925, 0.925],ExpressionUUID->"c9d2fec2-1d93-4baf-80bf-6da563597f45"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Axes3D",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " may also specify the axis system using Euler angles (see below). "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.641461021150572*^9, 3.641461039212177*^9}, {
  3.641461078062792*^9, 3.641461084762906*^9}, {3.641654339181566*^9, 
  3.641654340193672*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  1, 0.925, 0.925],ExpressionUUID->"8c37216f-81e6-494c-96c3-cced29c2f611"]
}, Open  ]],

