nStyleBox[\\\",\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"\
tensor\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\",\\\",\\\
nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"opts\\\",\\nFontSlant->\
\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"]\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\
\\) generates a \
\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"Graphics3D\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\) \
object representing a rank-2 spherical tensor, centred  at position \\!\\(\\*\
\\nStyleBox[\\\"r\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\). The \
\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"tensor\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\) may be a \
\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"SphericalTensor\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\) \
object of rank 2, or a 3\[Times]3 real matrix. In the case of a 3\[Times]3 \
real matrix, the traceless symmetric part of the matrix is extracted in order \
to define the rank-2 spherical tensor. If the vector \
\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"r\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\) is omitted, \
the value \
\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"r\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\\
nStyleBox[\\\" \
\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"=\\\",\\\
nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\" \\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\
\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"{\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\\
)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"0\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\\
nStyleBox[\\\",\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"\
0\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\",\\\",\\\
nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"0\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\
\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"}\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\\
) is assumed. The options may include rules for \
\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"OvaloidScale\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\
\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\",\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\) \
\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"OvaloidColors\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\
\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\",\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\\
nStyleBox[\\\" \
\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)and\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\" \
\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"\
OvaloidIsotropicComponent\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\\
nStyleBox[\\\".\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\) The option \
\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"OvaloidIsotropicComponent\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"\
Italic\\\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"\[Rule]\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\
\"]\\)\\!\\(\\*\\nStyleBox[\\\"iso\\\",\\nFontSlant->\\\"Italic\\\"]\\), \
incorporates an isotropic component in the graphical depiction of the tensor. \
See the usage messages for these options. The ovaloid graphical \
representation is described by Len Mueller in \
https://doi.org/10.1002/mrc.4793 and used in his program TensorView, \
https://sites.google.com/ucr.edu/Mueller/home/tensorview\\n\"\>", 
